        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 1:28PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>Temperatures rising into the upper 90s combined with high
humidity will produce heat indices of 105 to 108 this afternoon
across inland Georgia and South Carolina. If heat indices are
expected to remain above 108 degrees for 2 hours or more, a Heat
Advisory will be issued.
</description>
        <instruction>Take extra precautions if you work or spend time outside. When
possible, reschedule strenuous activities to early morning or
evening. Know the signs and symptoms of heat exhaustion and heat
stroke. Wear light weight and loose fitting clothing when
possible and drink plenty of water.</instruction>
